        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued April 23 at 4:27PM MDT until April 23 at 5:00PM MDT by NWS Goodland KS</headline>
        <description>At 427 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 11 miles southeast
of Towner, or 14 miles southwest of Tribune, moving northeast at 10
mph.

HAZARD...Golf ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Trained weather spotter reported golf ball sized hail in
southwestern Greeley county.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect wind
damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

This severe thunderstorm will remain over mainly rural areas of
southern Greeley County.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
